The French government plans newlegislation this year which will lower the thresholds at whichinvestors in companies must declare their shareholdings, Bourseofficials said.    The new rules, part of a scheme to provide more openness incorporate ownership structure, will lower the initialdeclaration threshold to five pct of a company's capital.    Under current rules, an investor has to notify the Boursesupervisory commission when a holding exceeds 10 pct, and againat 33 pct and 50 pct. The officials said a 20 pct level hasalso been added to the scale. Reuter&#3;